cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object tracking in videos. The use of attention and recurrent models also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The fact that it is a fully differentiable model that can be trained using gradient methods suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of auxiliary tasks to improve training convergence suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
